lar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Robert Waddeley x was born about 1404, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Robert Waddeley before 1425, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1404–No Date Given":"umbes 1404–Surnud","1410–Male":"1410–Surnud","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1404–Female":"1404–Surnud","1404":"1404","1425":"1425","1410":"1410","Abt 1404":"umbes 1404","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1404–No Date Given":"noin 1404–Kuollut","1410–Male":"1410–Kuollut","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1404–Female":"1404–Kuollut","1404":"1404","1425":"1425","1410":"1410","Abt 1404":"noin 1404","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1404–No Date Given":"environ 1404–Décédée","1410–Male":"1410–Décédé","1425–Female":"1425–Décédée","1404–Female":"1404–Décédée","1404":"1404","1425":"1425","1410":"1410","Abt 1404":"environ 1404","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lady Robert Waddeley x est née environ 1404, à Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Robert Waddeley avant 1425, à Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"Abt 1404–No Date Given":"um 1404–Verstorben","1410–Male":"1410–Verstorben","1425–Female":"1425–Verstorben","1404–Female":"1404–Verstorben","1404":"1404","1425":"1425","1410":"1410","Abt 1404